&lt;p&gt;React has been around for over ten years now, and thanks to its status as the most popular front-end framework, its ecosystem keeps growing and evolving. While React itself focuses just on the UI layer, most real world apps need more functionalities like data fetching, state management, form handling, animations, and routing. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is why a mature ecosystem matters, you don‚Äôt need to learn or code everything. There are many reliable and helpful tools that you can use right away.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are 8 tools and libraries that I think every React developer should know about. Whether you‚Äôre just starting out or you‚Äôve built production apps, these tools can save you time, reduce bugs, and make your codebase much more maintainable.&lt;/p&gt;

